<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rodman Takes Leave From Lakers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- The Dennis Rodman show with the Los  
Angeles Lakers has become a no-show. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman was granted an indefinite leave of absence for  
unspecified personal reasons just as the team began a road trip of 
six games in nine days. 
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers confirmed Sunday that the eccentric rebounding  
champion missed practice the day before. He took his leave before 
the team's flight to Sacramento for Sunday night's game against the 
Kings. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not going to freak out about it,'' Lakers coach Kurt  
Rambis said after a brief talk with Rodman following Saturday's 
practice. ``It's just something we're going to have to deal with.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rambis said ``nothing got resolved'' in his conversation with  
Rodman. He declined further comment on possible reasons for 
Rodman's move. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman's representatives did not immediately return calls.  
</P>
<P>
	Rambis does not know if Rodman will join the team on the road  
trip. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have no idea,'' Rambis said. ``You're asking me hypothetical  
questions for which I have no answers.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rambis added: ``If he's there, great; if he's not, then I just  
have to adjust.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rambis took over as coach of the Lakers last month on the same  
day Rodman began playing with the team. Following the firing of 
coach Del Harris and the signing of Rodman, the Lakers ran off 10 
straight victories. 
</P>
<P>
	Lakers spokesman John Black said Saturday that team executives  
Jerry West and Mitch Kupchak would not comment on Rodman's leave. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman, accompanied by two bodyguards, arrived at the Lakers'  
training site Saturday as practice was ending. He spoke briefly 
with Rambis behind the gymnasium at Southwest College and then 
drove off in his white Mercedes-Benz. 
</P>
<P>
	Lakers center Shaquille O'Neal knew Rodman had missed practice  
but did not know he was leaving the team. 
</P>
<P>
	``You work as hard as him (in games), I don't give a damn what  
you do in practice. ... I think you guys (reporters) want it to be 
a problem more than we do,'' O'Neal said. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman played on two championship teams in Detroit and three  
more with Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
	He has averaged 10.3 rebounds in nine games with the Lakers, but  
he sat out the second half of Friday's game against the Golden 
State Warriors because of a sore elbow. He also missed practice 
last Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Nobody really seems to worry about where Dennis is or what  
he's going to do,'' guard Derek Fisher said. ``We all knew what he 
was like before he signed. ... If he can afford to continue to pay 
the fines for missing or whatever, then that's his choice.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman, who turns 38 in May, delayed signing with the Lakers  
last month. He was upset at his relatively low salary under the 
NBA's new labor agreement. 
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers were unable to sign him for more than the veterans'  
minimum of $1 million, prorated to $600,000 for the shortened 
season and further reduced to $500,000 because of the 12 games the 
team had already played. 
</P>
<P>
	But one of the terms of Rodman's contract with Converse is that  
he receives $3 million if he plays in Los Angeles, Chicago or New 
York. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman's exceptional basketball skills have been accompanied by  
years of controversy. 
</P>
<P>
	There are his electric hair colors, multiple tattoos and body  
piercings as well as his cross-dressing inclinations. He also has 
been suspended while playing for Chicago for head-butting a referee 
and kicking a courtside photographer. He's infuriated coaches and 
teammates with missed practices and other antics. 
</P>
<P>
	Off the court, Rodman married actress Carmen Electra last  
November and split with agent Dwight Manley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
