walked to their game at Fresno State, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Heidi Jill Peterson, 40, a Gonzaga trainer, sustained a broken  
right leg in the Saturday accident, officer Julian Perea said. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzaga outfielder Brent Church was in serious but stable  
condition Saturday night, hospital officials said. Infielder Kevin 
Cave and outfielder Richard Urdahl were treated and released. 
</P>
<P>
	The team canceled its Saturday game against Seton Hall and a  
Sunday game at San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
	The players were walking from their hotel to Beiden Field for  
the game, school officials said. A motorist stopped to let the 
players cross a driveway, but a driver behind lost control, jumped 
the curb and plowed into the team, Perea said. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver was identified as Adam Charles Perry, 18. He was not  
injured and was not cited, police said. 
</P>
