<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Excellent Meeting Wins Santa Anita </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Excellent Meeting, a 1-10 betting  
favorite who might run next month in the Santa Anita Derby, held 
off a late rally by Tout Charmant to win the Santa Anita Oaks by 
just a neck Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory in the $250,000 race for 3-year-old fillies came  
under the urging of jockey Kent Desormeaux in the time of 1:43 1-5 
over 1 1-16 miles. 
</P>
<P>
	Excellent Meeting, who might be pointed toward the Kentucky  
Derby if she has success against the colts in the Santa Anita 
Derby, passed Tout Charmant at the half-mile mark. 
</P>
<P>
	The lead was 1 1/2 lengths before jockey David Flores and Tout  
Charmant made for a driving finish through the final sixteenth. 
</P>
<P>
	Gleefully, a 57-1 shot, finished third, 6 1/2 lengths back in a  
field of six. Each carried 117 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Tout Charmant had two previous wins and three seconds in five  
starts with earnings of $100,200 going into the race. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite the victory, Excellent Meeting's trainer, Bob Baffert,  
made no commitments for either the April 3 Santa Anita Derby or the 
Kentucky Derby on May 1. 
</P>
<P>
	Sunday's victory brought her record to 6-3-1 in 10 starts. The  
winner's share of $150,000 made her a millionaire. 
</P>
<P>
	Excellent Meeting paid $2.20, $2.20 and $2.10. Tout Charmant  
paid $2.60 and $2.10 as the 8-1 second favorite. 
</P>
<P>
	Owner John Mabee said he was a little disappointed in Excellent  
Meeting's performance. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was gutty enough to win, but I was disappointed in the  
fact that she wasn't able to handle that other filly in the last 
eighth-of-a-mile,'' he said. ``They've touted her as being a super 
filly, but all horses are inclined to have an off-day once in a 
while. So let's hope this was her off-day.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
