<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 5-Time Escapee Returned to Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLLINSVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Minutes before he was featured on  
``America's Most Wanted,'' a five-time prison escapee sentenced to 
more than 18 years behind bars in the fatal carjacking of a British 
military man was found hiding in the attic of a friend's rural 
home. 
</P>
<P>
	Roger Dale Yeadon, 26, escaped from a jail in Las Vegas, N.M.,  
Feb. 8. He, along with two other inmates who were later recaptured, 
shinnied up pipes leading to the jail's roof, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	He traveled to Alabama by bus and went to the northeast corner  
of his home state, where he has family. Authorities set up 
electronic listening posts and later used helicopters and tracking 
dogs in the search, said Mike Richards, a supervisor at the U.S. 
Marshal's office in Birmingham. 
</P>
<P>
	A tip Saturday night led them to the home in the rural community  
of Skirum, near Collinsville, said DeKalb County Sheriff Cecil 
Reed. The convict surrendered without resistance shortly after 7 
p.m. Fox's ``America's Most Wanted'' aired locally at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	Yeadon, who had grown a beard to alter his appearance, had a  
small pocket knife when captured, a handcuff key in his boot and 
was concealing a small amount of marijuana, Reed said. 
</P>
<P>
	He also had tried to alter a tattoo of the Ford Motor Co. logo  
``to make it look like ... bricks,'' said Tom Bustamante, chief 
deputy U.S. marshal in Albuquerque, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
	Yeadon was sentenced in January to more than 18 years in federal  
prison for the 1996 carjack slaying of Maj. David Graham Nichols, 
vice commander of the Defence School of Languages in England, who 
was killed en route to a conference at Kirtland Air Force Base in 
Albuquerque. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time of the carjacking, Yeadon was an escapee from  
Alabama. 
</P>
<P>
	His latest escape came at San Miguel County Jail in Las Vegas,  
N.M., where he was being held pending assignment to a federal 
prison. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
