<HEADLINE> McConaughey Acts Like Goofball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Up for the part of a goofball in ``Ed TV,''  
Matthew McConaughey showed his stuff after spilling his soda during 
the audition. Instead of wiping it up with a towel, he bent down 
and slurped it off the tabletop. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm always trying to buck the system,'' McConaughey says in  
Sunday's Daily News. ``I love being goofy. It turns out I'm most 
happy when I'm that way, and people like me the most when I'm that 
way.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 29-year-old actor, whose credits include ``A Time to Kill,''  
``Dazed and Confused'' and ``Lone Star,'' plays a guy who lets a 
camera crew follow him around 24 hours a day, hoping to be famous 
until he gets famous and learns about the flip side of fame. 
McConaughey's personal philosophy fit perfectly into the premise. 
</P>
<P>
	``Something I've learned about this business is that the more  
you can be yourself, the better,'' he says. ``There's only one of 
you, so you're a novelty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
