<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mob Comedy Rubs Out Competition / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``Analyze This,'' the mobster-in-therapy  
comedy with Robert De Niro and Billy Crystal, held off a flood of 
new movies to remain No. 1 at the box office for a second week, 
industry estimates showed Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Appealing to older audiences in a market full of teen fare,  
``Analyze This'' collected $15.7 million, down just 15 percent from 
its debut weekend. That put it far ahead of the second-place film, 
the belated horror sequel ``The Rage: Carrie 2,'' which opened with 
$7.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
	``Cruel Intentions,'' a mean love games story starring Sarah  
Michelle Gellar, tumbled 46 percent in its second week to finish 
third with $7 million, according to studio estimates for Friday 
through Sunday. Final numbers are released Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Rage,'' a followup to the original ``Carrie'' in 1976, led the  
five films that opened in wide release over the weekend. The other 
newcomers opened with fair to lackluster business, and the box 
office overall was once again down -- this time 6.3 percent -- from 
the same weekend last year, when ``Titanic'' was sailing onto Oscar 
victories and record grosses. 
</P>
<P>
	One mild surprise was ``Baby Geniuses,'' which opened in fifth  
with $5.8 million despite unfavorable reviews. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Corrupter,'' pairing Hong Kong action star Chow Yun-Fat  
with Mark Wahlberg, debuted with $5.9 million for fourth, ``The 
Deep End of the Ocean'' starring Michelle Pfeiffer opened with $5.6 
million for sixth and the movie version of the computer game ``Wing 
Commander'' was seventh with $5 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Rounding out the top 10 were ``The Other Sister,'' which had  
$3.9 million for eighth, ``8mm'' fell to $3.6 million for ninth and 
``October Sky'' was tenth with $3.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Here are estimated grosses at North American theaters.  
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Analyze This,'' $15.7 million.  
</P>
<P>
	2. ``The Rage: Carrie 2,'' $7.4 million.  
</P>
<P>
	3. ``Cruel Intentions,'' $7 million.  
</P>
<P>
	4. ``The Corruptor,'' $5.9 million.  
</P>
<P>
	5. ``Baby Geniuses,'' $5.8 million.  
</P>
<P>
	6. ``The Deep End of the Ocean,'' $5.6 million.  
</P>
<P>
	7. ``Wing Commander,'' $5 million.  
</P>
<P>
	8. ``The Other Sister,'' $3.9 million.  
</P>
<P>
	9. ``8mm,'' $3.6 million.  
</P>
<P>
	10. ``October Sky,'' $3.1 million.  
</P>
</TEXT>
