<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Gain on Nissan News / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese stocks gained early Monday, boosted by a  
surge in Nissan Motor's share price on speculation that France's 
Renault was close to purchasing a stake in the automaker. The U.S. 
dollar slipped against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average rose 70.13 points,  
or 0.45 percent, to close the morning session at 15,558.99 points. 
On Friday, the average closed down 13.28 points, or 0.09 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 119.27 yen in early trading, down 0.77 yen  
from late Friday in Tokyo but above its late New York level of 
118.78 yen on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 129.70 yen, down  
from 131.35 yen late Friday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, share prices started lower after the  
government released data Friday showing that Japan's economy shrank 
0.8 percent in the October-December quarter of 1998, analysts said. 
</P>
<P>
	The numbers were worse than economists had predicted and marked  
the fifth straight quarter -- the first time ever -- that Japan's 
gross domestic product had contracted. 
</P>
<P>
	But the market recovered as troubled Nissan Motor's share price  
surged 46 yen ($0.39), or 11.5 percent, to 447 yen ($3.75) on 
speculation that the company is close to a tie-up with Renault. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal would allow the French auto maker to take a stake of up  
to 40 percent in Nissan and supply three board members. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, Nissan Motor said in a statement that the two  
companies were studying the possibility of a deal, but that no 
formal proposal for an alliance had been received from Renault. 
</P>
<P>
	The possibility of a deal is also helping shares of Nissan  
Diesel. 
</P>
<P>
	``If Nissan gets off the hook and can reduce its debt through  
capital from Renault, it will be in more of a position to help 
Nissan Diesel,'' said Chuck Lambert, market analyst at Jardine 
Fleming Securities. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section gained 0.62 points, or 0.05 percent, to 1,196.23 
points. The TOPIX closed down 0.57 points, or 0.05 percent, on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	On the foreign exchange market, the dollar remained under  
selling pressure against the yen after the Japanese currency moved 
higher against the euro on Friday, analysts said. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
