<DOCNO> APW19990314.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-14 15:52:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kimberlite Pipe Wins in Louisiana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Kimberlite Pipe, a 21-1 outsider, battled on  
the rail to hold off highly regarded Answer Lively and Ecton Park 
and win the Louisiana Derby on Sunday at the Fair Grounds. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory in the $600,000-added race for 3-year-olds came  
under the urging of jockey Robbie Albarado in the time of 1:43 4-5 
over 1 1-16th miles and earned the colt's owners, Prairie Star 
Racing and John Gunther, $384,489. 
</P>
<P>
	More so, by defeating Answer Lively and Ecton Park the victory  
moved Kimberlite Pipe a step closer to a possible run in the 
Kentucky Derby. 
</P>
<P>
	The last time Kimberlite Pipe ran, he finished third to Ecton  
Park and Answer Lively at 1/16th-miles at the Fair Grounds. 
</P>
<P>
	But on Sunday, Albarado kept his mount no less than three  
lengths off the pace through the final turn. And when the outside 
closers made their move, Albarado had to take his mount to the 
rail. 
</P>
<P>
	At the 16th pole, Kimberlite Pipe found room and put a nose  
ahead of Answer Lively. He then held on to win by a head. 
</P>
<P>
	Kimberlite Pipe paid $45.40, $11.80 and $8.60. Answer Lively  
paid $4 and $3.60 to place and Ecton Park $4. 
</P>
<P>
	Favorite General Challenge, trained by Bob Baffert, lunged at  
the start and fell quickly behind. Trailing the eight-horse field 
most of the way, jockey Gary Stevens' mount had too much ground to 
make up. 
</P>
<P>
	General Challenge was forced to run wide on the final turn and  
finished with little drive in the fifth position. 
</P>
<P>
	A foul claim against Albarado and Pat Day aboard Answer Lively,  
lodged by rider Billy Patin after his mount, Valhol, finished 
fourth, was disallowed by the stewards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
