<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Spielberg Honored for 'Pvt. Ryan' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) -- Steven Spielberg's ``Saving Private  
Ryan'' won the 1998 American Cinema Editors award for best feature 
film editing. 
</P>
<P>
	The brutally realistic World War II story edited by Michael Kahn  
beat fellow Academy Award contenders ``Shakespeare in Love'' and 
``The Thin Red Line,'' as well as ``Out of Sight'' and ``The Horse 
Whisperer.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Saving Private Ryan'' has already won top honors from the  
Producers Guild and the Directors Guild of America, as well as 
Golden Globes for best director and best dramatic film. 
</P>
<P>
	French Stewart of ``3rd Rock From the Sun'' was master of  
ceremonies for the 49th annual ``Eddie'' Awards Saturday night at 
the Beverly Hilton Hotel. The awards recognize excellence in both 
film and television editing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
