<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Corrects RJR-Philip Morris Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- The Associated Press on March 12  
incorrectly characterized one claim in a federal lawsuit filed by 
R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Co. against Philip Morris. 
</P>
<P>
	The lawsuit alleges Philip Morris provides lucrative discounts  
to retailers that give the company 100 percent of a store's visible 
retail space all the time, not three months out of the year as the 
story said. 

</P>
</TEXT>
